Description: Alminder is focused on developing Mynd Calendar, an intelligent mobile calendar app for iPhones and other iOS devices.
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Alminder, Inc. makes Mynd Calendar, an intelligent mobile calendar app for iPhone that acts like a virtual assistant, making your life easier at home and work and saving you time.  It learns where you spend your time and who you meet along the way, becoming increasingly helpful the more you use it. It syncs with all of your existing calendars and can be used instead of your Apple calendar on your iPhone. Unlike other so-called 'smart calendars,' Mynd Calendar's sophisticated algorithms identify the places you're going within the content of your calendar events and accurately predict (even in advance) how much buffer time you need to schedule between meetings given the typical traffic at that time of day.  As you get closer to your appointments, Mynd Calendar tells you when to leave, based on current traffic conditions and launches your favorite navigation app to get you to your appointment on time.   Mynd Calendar also: -Notifies you when you're running late and lets you easily email, call or text the people who need to know from within the calendar. -Automatically identifies conference call numbers and facilitates easy, one-click dial-in. -Discovers the people listed in your calendar events and looks up their LinkedIn profiles and information from your address book, so you know who you’re meeting with and can get in touch with them directly from your calendar. -Pulls in your relevant Evernote notes so that you're always prepared for your next meeting. -RSVP to meeting invites. -Tells you the weather at both where you are and where you're going.
Industry Groups: Events, Media and Entertainment, Mobile, Software
Founders: Max Wheeler, Scott Putterman, Tony Robinson

ClearTrial software provides life sciences companies with the ability to: -Conduct rapid "what-if" scenario planning for clinical development -Optimize clinical trials according to business goals -Conduct more trials with less cost and effort -Obtain accurate cost & resource forecasts -Streamline sponsor/CRO negotiations -Gain visibility and control over clinical project status To accomplish this, the ClearTrial software architecture follows a project management methodology that includes activity-based costing, which predicts the level of effort for a specific resource (person) to perform a given task (activity). Full Description: The cover story in the October 2013 Harvard Business Review was "Consulting on the Cusp of Disruption".  Finally, someone was shining a light on one of the last industries yet to be disrupted by technology!!! Over the past 15 years, the co-founders of ConsultantGo have had a front-row seat as the stars aligned to reshape the $435B consulting industry.  They were at Arthur Andersen Consulting when the Enron scandal occurred.  They have been active in the "independent consulting movement".  And now they are building the marketplace of the future.   Using proprietary data models, business intelligence and personality profiling, ConsultantGo simplifies the process of finding the right consultant from weeks to seconds.  This helps clients and staffing firms locate the right person quickly -- and helps consultants "be found" quickly to minimize costs and downtime.   ConsultantGo is a no-brainer for any consultant, staffing firm or company that uses consultants.  Additionally, it's a natural fit for baby-boomers and retirees that want to consult, but don't know how to start. Description: HoverWind LLC (HW)was formed to become the market leader in manufacturing and distribution of Personal Hovercraft.
Headquarters Regions: Tampa Bay Area, East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: HoverWind LLC  (HW)was formed to become the market leader in manufacturing and distribution of Personal Hovercraft .  Hovercraft’s unique advantage is the ability to travel over widely diverse terrain. They literally “hover” over land, water, mud, ice and other surfaces, both at speed and when stationary. Hovercraft can transport higher payloads, with less horsepower and fuel, than any other mechanized craft.  There are no other powered vehicles that provide the versatility of hovercraft … OR THE FUN! HW will initiate operations as the only hovercraft dealer of hovercraft in the State of Florida through exclusive dealership relationships with the two of the three leading recreational hovercraft manufacturers in North America.  HW has formed relationships with two of these entities effectively ‘rolling up’ two thirds of the domestic competition and the largest manufacturer in the United Kingdom and is in position to build and dominate the market for Personal Hovercraft. The US market for their hovercraft overlaps three segments of the Power Sports market, Personal Watercraft (Jet Skis), Snowmobiles and All Terrain Vehicles, in addition to segments of the Recreational Boat market. These segments generate approximately $4 billion in annual sales. Jet Skis and Snowmobiles are the most applicable segments. Jet Skis and Snowmobiles generated US sales of $987 million in 2013. HW will initially focus on these market segments by being the first to raise awareness of the fun, excitement and utility found by owning a Personal Hovercraft. For the last thirty years there has been no serious new product introductions in the Power Sports market. HW intends to fully invigorate this market. The Company initiated an Offering of its Units in a Private Placement Memorandum dated September 2, 2014.  The PPM, Executive Summary, Term Sheet and detailed financial pro forma are available to accredited investors upon request.
